<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Macroscopic description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
Cap 1.0-2.2 cm in diameter, convex to umbonate, sometimes umbilicate, margin smooth, tacky when moist, occasionally hygrophanous, unicolored, sometimes bicolored, at center sepia to fuscous or dark brick, at margin pinkish buff to clay pink to cinnamon, sometimes quite thin margin, without remains of universal veil, partial veil present. Lamellae initially light clay, at maturity slightly more brownish, attachment emarginate, maximum depth 3-5 mm, number of lamellae {L} 18-35, droplets absent, white fimbriate edge sometimes present but weak. Stem (1.5-)1.9-3.1(-3.7) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.2-0.3(-0.5) cm, light watery brownish, darker towards base, cylindrical, stem Q (5-)8-12.7(-16.5), fibrillose, usually pruinose at apex. Context firm, stem interior stuffed, later hollow, stem flesh variably discoloring from base. Smell raphanoid sometimes strongly. Taste weakly raphanoid. Spore deposit sepia.
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/mycokeys.79.63363.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/533411" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" start="Figure 20" startId="F20">
