<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hymenogastraceae" genus="Hebeloma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hebeloma" order="Ostropales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Hebeloma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sect. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Denudata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Denudata" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Denudata</taxonomicName>
(Fr.) Sacc.; Fl. Ital. Crypt. I 15: 691, 1916.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Veil absent. Cap uni- or bicolored. Lamellae often exuding small hyaline or colored drops. Cheilocystidia long, swollen in the apical part, constricted in the median part, basal part swollen or not. Spores amygdaloid to limoniform, ornamented, sometimes strongly.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
